title: OnceFeatures
position: 572,377
tags: tutorial once
---
Guide: Let me show you the "once" statement!

// --- BASIC ONCE BLOCK ---
// Content inside <<once>> only shows the first time
<<once>>
    Guide: This is my first-time-only greeting!
    Guide: You'll never see these lines again.
<<endonce>>

// --- ONCE WITH ELSE ---
// Show different content on repeat visits
<<once>>
    Guide: Welcome, new visitor!
<<else>>
    Guide: Welcome back, returning visitor!
<<endonce>>

// --- ONCE IF (conditional once) ---
// Only runs once AND only when condition is true
<<declare $is_vip = true>>
Guide: As a VIP, you get this special one-time message! <<once if $is_vip>>

// --- INLINE ONCE ON DIALOGUE ---
// Put <<once>> at end of line to show it only once
Guide: Have you been here before? <<once>>
Guide: This line always shows.

// --- INLINE ONCE IF ON DIALOGUE ---
Guide: Thanks for having a sword! <<once if $has_sword>>

// --- ONCE ON OPTIONS ---
Guide: What would you like to know?

-> What's your name? <<once>>
    Guide: I'm your Guide! But you already asked that...
-> Tell me a secret <<once>>
    Guide: The cake is a lie. Don't ask again!
-> How's the weather? <<once if $sunny>>
    Guide: It's sunny! But I only comment on weather once.
-> Regular question (always available)
    Guide: You can ask this anytime!

Guide: The "once" statement is great for:
Guide: - First-time greetings
Guide: - Tutorial messages that shouldn't repeat
Guide: - One-time secrets or rewards
Guide: - Options that disappear after being chosen

<<jump Menu>>
===

